4j8.text:
Let $H$ be a subgroup of $G$. 
Then for any two [4j4 left cosets] of $H$ in $G$, there is a [-499] between the two cosets.

# Proof

Let $aH, bH$ be two cosets.
Define the function $f: aH \to bH$ by $x \mapsto b a^{-1} x$.

This has the correct [3lg codomain]: if $x \in aH$ (so $x = ah$, say), then $ba^{-1} a x = bx$ so $f(x) \in bH$.

The function is [4b7 injective]: if $b a^{-1} x = b a^{-1} y$ then (pre-multiplying both sides by $a b^{-1}$) we obtain $x = y$.

The function is [4bg surjective]: given $b h \in b H $, we want to find $x \in aH$ such that $f(x) = bh$.
Let $x = a h$ to obtain $f(x) = b a^{-1} a h = b h$, as required.
